  "prompt": "What universities does Scivac Therapeutics recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Scivac Therapeutics, like many companies in the biotech and pharmaceutical industries, typically recruits new graduates from universities with strong programs in life sciences, biomedicine, engineering, and related fields. While specific university partnerships or recruitment preferences may not be publicly disclosed, they generally target top-tier institutions known for their research and academic excellence.\n\n**Universities they may recruit from include:**\n- Ivy League schools (e.g., Harvard, MIT, Stanford, Johns Hopkins)\n- Leading public universities (e.g., UC Berkeley, UCLA, University of Michigan)\n- Specialized institutions with strong life science programs (e.g., Caltech, UCSF, UNC Chapel Hill)\n- International universities with renowned research programs (e.g., University of Cambridge, ETH Zurich, National University of Singapore)\n\n**Majors they typically look for:**\n- **Life Sciences**: Biology, Biochemistry, Molecular Biology, Pharmacology, Immunology\n- **Engineering**: Bioengineering, Chemical Engineering, Biomedical Engineering\n- **Chemistry**: Organic Chemistry, Medicinal Chemistry, Analytical Chemistry\n- **Data Science/Computational Biology**: Bioinformatics, Computational Chemistry, Data Science\n- **Business/Regulatory Affairs**: Biotechnology Management, Regulatory Science, Pharmaceutical Sciences\n\nScivac Therapeutics is likely to seek candidates with a strong academic background, research experience, and relevant skills for roles in drug discovery, development, manufacturing, or commercialization. Networking events, career fairs, and university partnerships are common avenues for recruitment. For precise details, it\u2019s best to check their official job postings or career page.",
